&lt;p&gt;When there are two windows side by side, this red line disappears.&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3134/why-is-there-a-red-line-on-the-right-side-of-the-screen/?answer=3135#post-id-3135</link><description>It does not have an own paragraph in the userguide, but in the [colors section](http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_changing_colors) you can read about the _indicator_. 

&gt; The **indicator** color is used for
&gt; indicating where a new window will be
&gt; opened. For horizontal split
&gt; containers, the right border will be
&gt; painted in indicator color, for
&gt; vertical split containers, the bottom
&gt; border. This only applies to single
&gt; windows within a split container,
&gt; which are otherwise indistinguishable
&gt; from single windows outside of a split
&gt; container.</description><pubDate>Mon, 30 Dec 2013 21:05:38 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3134/why-is-there-a-red-line-on-the-right-side-of-the-screen/?answer=3135#post-id-3135</guid></item></channel></rss>